The AWS JavaScript SDK natively supports promises. Instead of this:

    s3.listObjectsV2(params, function (err, data) {
        // do something with data here in the callback
    });

write this:

    const data = await s3.listObjectsV2(params).promise();
    // do something with data here

Note that `await` may only be used in an `async` function. If you aren&#39;t in an async function then you can fabricate one as follows (an immediately invoked async arrow function):

    (async () =&gt; {
        const data = await s3.listObjectsV2(params).promise();
        // do something with data here
    })();

